  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HDB Barging</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hidrovias do Brasil S.A (HDB) is developing a barge operation in the Paraguay-Parana river system in South America through a wholly owned Uruguay-based subsidiary. The Project consists of the acquisition, operation and maintenance of a push boat and barge fleet for the transport of iron ore from Corumba in Brazil down the river system for consumption and export. The Project is expected to deploy 8 convoys in the river system with an estimated annual capacity of over 3 million tons.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed IFC investment will help to: (i)	increase the supply of efficient, low emission transport services on the Parana-Paraguay River System; (ii)	increase competition in the barging sector, encouraging operators to improve efficiency and reliability of service; (iii)	 create additional employment for the region; (iv)	foster South-South investments; and (v)	improve supply chain management and support the development of the iron ore and steel industries in the region with follow-on benefits for construction and industrial sectors.</narrative>
  </description>
